# Environment Variables

## Server Configuration
PORT=5174
NODE_ENV=development
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

## Email Configuration (IMPORTANT - Required for contact form emails)

# Gmail Setup (Recommended):
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication in Google Account
# 2. Go to: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Generate an App Password (select Mail and Windows Computer)
# 4. Copy the 16-character password and paste below

SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-16-character-app-password

# Where to send contact form submissions
CONTACT_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com

# Alternative Email Providers:
# Outlook/Hotmail: smtp-mail.outlook.com:587
# Yahoo: smtp.mail.yahoo.com:587
# SendGrid: smtp.sendgrid.net:587 (use 'apikey' as username)

## Database (Optional - for MongoDB integration)
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/portfolio
# Or use MongoDB Atlas:
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/portfolio

## JWT Secret (Optional - for future authentication)
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-key-here

## Web3Forms (Frontend-only contact form)
# Get your free access key at https://web3forms.com/
VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=your-access-key-here

## Production Notes:
# - Use strong, unique JWT_SECRET in production
# - Never commit .env file to git
# - Use environment variables in deployment platform
# - For Vercel/Railway/Render: Set these in their dashboard

